From: DatanoiseTV <noreply@datanoise.tv>
Subject: [PATCH] ASoC: dwc: fix TDM master mode clock configuration

The DesignWare I2S CCR (Clock Configuration Register) only accepted
frame lengths of 32, 48, or 64, which made TDM master mode with more
than 2 slots impossible. When using 8 TDM slots at 32-bit width the
required bclk_ratio is 256, which was rejected with -EINVAL.

In TDM mode the CCR should reflect the per-slot word length (always
32-bit for this IP), not the total frame length. The actual BCLK rate
must account for the total number of slots.

This patch:
 - Detects active TDM mode and sets CCR based on slot width
 - Computes BCLK as sample_rate * slots * slot_width for TDM
 - Falls back to the original logic for standard I2S mode

Tested on Raspberry Pi 5 (RP1 DesignWare I2S) with 8-slot TDM in
master mode at 48kHz and 96kHz.

Signed-off-by: DatanoiseTV <noreply@datanoise.tv>
---
 sound/soc/dwc/dwc-i2s.c | 30 ++++++++++++++++++++++++------
 1 file changed, 24 insertions(+), 6 deletions(-)

diff --git a/sound/soc/dwc/dwc-i2s.c b/sound/soc/dwc/dwc-i2s.c
index XXXXXXX..XXXXXXX 100644
--- a/sound/soc/dwc/dwc-i2s.c
+++ b/sound/soc/dwc/dwc-i2s.c
@@ -399,8 +399,28 @@ static int dw_i2s_hw_params(struct snd_pcm_substream *substream,
 	if (dev->capability & DW_I2S_MASTER) {
 		u32 frame_length = config->data_width * 2;

-		if (dev->bclk_ratio)
-			frame_length = dev->bclk_ratio;
+		if (dev->tdm_slots) {
+			/*
+			 * In TDM mode, CCR configures the per-slot word
+			 * length, not the total frame. The hardware uses
+			 * IER[TDM_SLOTS] to determine the frame structure.
+			 * Force CCR to match the 32-bit slot width.
+			 */
+			frame_length = dev->tdm_slots * config->data_width;
+
+			dev->ccr = 0x10; /* 64-bit word pair (32-bit per slot) */
+
+			u32 bitclk = config->sample_rate * frame_length;
+			int ret2 = clk_set_rate(dev->clk, bitclk);
+			if (ret2) {
+				dev_err(dev->dev,
+					"Can't set TDM I2S clock rate %u: %d\n",
+					bitclk, ret2);
+				return ret2;
+			}
+			i2s_write_reg(dev->i2s_base, CCR, dev->ccr);
+			return 0;
+		}
+
+		if (dev->bclk_ratio) frame_length = dev->bclk_ratio;

 		switch (frame_length) {
 		case 32:
--
